					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Proverbs.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="175v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Mishle</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש משלי</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The pointed Hebrew text, accompanied by an Arabic translation, is embodied.</p>
								<p>Contains chapters: 19:10-15, 19:23-20:8, 20:17-21:13, 21:14-23:19, 23:22-25:2, 25:4-26:6, 26:10-28, 27:4-15, 27:17-30:6, 30:8-16, 30:23-31:11, 31:15-20. 31:26-31 (imperfect at the end).</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text the following parts are preserved: 19:10-16, 19:23-20:8, 20:18-21:13, 21:15-23:20, 23:23-25:2, 25:6-26:7, 26:11-28, 27:5-15, 27:!8-30:7, 30:10-31:31.</p>
								<p>Has a scribal subscription at the beginning.</p>
								<p>Masoretic division into section and קרי are marked in the margins.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Wechsler_2003" type="page">283-310</ref>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<filiation>Uniform with Or 2506, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">293</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>175 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>174</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>130</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>175 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>21 quires, originally of 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic numerals on the upper margin of the first page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios: 5, 13, 27, 58, 78, 93, 101, 111, 149, 157, 172, 173.</p>
									<p>Imperfect at the end.</p>
									<p>Many folios stained or water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="14" writtenLines="14">
									<p>The numbers of the chapters have been added by a later hand.</p>
									<p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
